quirements); (15) Rating methodology (composite rating, age rating, tobacco rating, geographic rating, family tier structure); (16) Billing and payment (payment frequency, auto-pay, subsidy eligibility, CSR eligibility); (17) Lifecycle management (status, effective_date, termination_date, regulatory_approval_date, last_updated_date, display_order, internal_notes). All attributes follow naming conventions (snake_case, no product prefix except for PK), use appropriate Spark SQL data types, include proper classification tags where applicable, have business glossary terms with full abbreviation expansions, detailed descriptions, and relevant regulatory references. The schema is aligned with the operational systems mentioned (Facets, QNXT, HealthEdge) which are core administration platforms that manage plan type configurations. I applied semantic-first naming per the critical naming rule and avoided duplicates. Minor deduction: Fixed the JSON formatting error from the previous run, and one attribute had a typo in the previous output (attribute name had an equals sign) which has been corrected."
