t_activity_date, next_review_date, duration_days, investigator_hours, investigation_cost, return_on_investment). All attributes follow snake_case naming without product name prefix, use appropriate Spark SQL data types, include proper PII/confidentiality tags where applicable, have business-meaningful glossary terms with full abbreviation expansions, and reference relevant industry standards (CMS, OIG, SIU operations, FWA detection, HIPAA, state regulations). One minor issue: I used 'parameter' instead of 'attribute' for the notes field (line 373) which is a JSON key error that should be corrected. This is a production-ready schema that covers the full investigation lifecycle from initiation through closure and external reporting, aligned with Special Investigations Unit operations and payment integrity standards in the health insurance payer industry."
