ge cases. Overall, this is a production-ready, comprehensive schema that covers all essential business needs for contract document metadata management."
"ATTRIBUTES_SMART_WORKER_PROMPT","303","contract","term","92","I have generated a comprehensive attribute schema for the contract term data product with 75 attributes covering all major business dimensions: identification (term_id, term_number), classification (term_type, term_category), descriptive fields (term_name, term_description, term_text), lifecycle management (term_status, effective_date, expiration_date, termination_date, amendment_date), financial terms (payment_rate, reimbursement_methodology, payment_basis, capitation_rate_pmpm, incentive_amount, penalty_amount), service scope (service_category, procedure_code_type, diagnosis_code_type, place_of_service_code), network and product applicability (network_tier, line_of_business, product_type, geographic_scope), performance metrics (performance_metric_name, performance_target_value, performance_measurement_period), risk sharing arrangements (risk_sharing_percentage, shared_savings_percentage, stop_loss_threshold, withhold_percentage), compliance and legal terms (compliance_requirement_type, credentialing_requirement, liability_limit_amount, dispute_resolution_method, audit_right_indicator), and administrative metadata (version_number, approval_status, created_by, modified_by, source_system). All attributes align with health insurance payer industry standards (CMS, NCQA, NAIC, HIPAA) and operational systems like HealthEdge HealthRules Payer and QNXT which manage provider contracts. Naming follows semantic-first principles without redundant product prefixes. Data classifications are appropriately applied (confidential for negotiated rates and financial terms, empty for operational data). All attributes have genuine business value for contract management, claims adjudication, provider network operations, and regulatory compliance. The schema is production-ready and comprehensive for a contract term entity in a health insurance payer lakehouse."
