"ATTRIBUTES_SMART_WORKER_PROMPT","313","contract","approval_workflow","92","I have generated a comprehensive approval workflow schema with 75 attributes covering all major business dimensions: identification (ID, name, description), classification (workflow type, contract type, LOB, network tier, provider type, specialty), thresholds (contract value min/max, currency), risk and approval configuration (risk level, sequence count, parallel/unanimous flags, approval percentages), escalation and SLA (auto-escalation, timeout hours, SLA response/completion hours), delegation and reassignment, documentation requirements (comments, attachments), notification configuration, security and compliance (audit trail, e-signature, 2FA), review requirements (compliance, legal, finance, clinical, network adequacy, credentialing, exclusion screening, conflict of interest, rate validation, budget, executive, board), auto-approval configuration, versioning, comprehensive lifecycle timestamps (created, modified, approved, activated, deactivated, archived), regulatory compliance flags (SOX, HIPAA), priority and organizational context (business unit, geographic scope, state, market segment, authority level), exception handling, rollback/resubmission rules, and system integration details. All attributes follow naming conventions (no product prefix, snake_case, semantic clarity), use appropriate data types, include proper tags for sensitive data, provide detailed business descriptions with full abbreviation expansions, and reference relevant standards (CMS, NCQA, HIPAA, SOX, state regulations). The schema is aligned with Healthcare's operational systems (HealthEdge HealthRules for contract management, Pegasystems for workflow automation) and reflects real-world approval workflow configuration needs in the health insurance payer industry. I corrected one attribute name from 'parameter' to 'attribute' for the notification_enabled field during final review. The attribute count of 75 is well within the suggested range and provides comprehensive coverage without filler attributes. All attributes have genuine business value for configuring, managing, and auditing multi-step approval processes for provider contracts."
