"ATTRIBUTES_SMART_WORKER_PROMPT","316","contract","agreement_version","92","I have generated a comprehensive schema for the agreement_version data product with 99 attributes covering all major aspects of provider contracting in health insurance: identification, versioning, provider details, reimbursement methodologies, risk arrangements, quality requirements, compliance provisions, operational terms, contact information, and audit trails. The schema aligns with Healthcare's operational systems (HealthEdge HealthRules Payer for provider contracts) and incorporates industry-standard terminology (NPI, TIN, LOB, PMPM, ACO, PCMH, HEDIS, etc.). All attributes follow naming conventions (snake_case, no product prefix except PK), use appropriate data types, include proper PII/confidentiality tags, and reference relevant governing bodies (CMS, HIPAA, NCQA, NAIC, etc.). I identified one minor structural error during self-review: attribute 'hipaa_compliance_attestation_flag' was mistakenly labeled as 'parameter' instead of 'attribute' in the JSON key, which I corrected. The schema comprehensively covers contract lifecycle, financial terms, quality/compliance requirements, operational provisions, and administrative details that a contract management professional would expect. Deducting 8 points for the single JSON key error that required correction."
