"IN_DOMAIN_LINKING_SMART_PROMPT","22","marketing","*","92","Complete analysis of all 18 products in marketing domain. All products now have at least one relationship (inbound or outbound). Identified 15 genuinely new FK links that were missing. Key additions: vendor_contract→vendor (critical missing link), multiple compliance_approval FKs to formalize approval tracking, marketing_schedule links to campaign/segment/vendor, and offer/asset links to audience_segment. No bidirectional violations, no self-references, no cross-domain links, no re-inclusion of existing FKs. Used candidate_evaluation properly - all 15 links in output were marked INCLUDE. Conservative on M:N detection - marketing_channel appears to be a reference table with string-based usage rather than true FK relationships in current model. The 'channel' attributes throughout are STRING types storing channel names directly, not FKs, so no M:N relationship exists in current implementation. Minor uncertainty on whether marketing_channel should have been linked (decided against based on STRING attribute pattern), but this is a reasonable architectural judgment. All structural rules followed."
