"IN_DOMAIN_LINKING_SMART_PROMPT","26","shared","*","92","Complete analysis of all 26 products in the shared domain. All products are now connected with at least one relationship (inbound or outbound). Candidate_evaluation was populated before links array with systematic evaluation of all potential in-domain relationships. No self-referencing links, no bidirectional violations, no existing FK re-inclusions, no cross-domain links. All 22 links in the output array were marked INCLUDE in candidate_evaluation. Conservative decisions were made on several borderline relationships (e.g., formulary↔formulary_tier was excluded because formulary_tier is a reference table, not a child of a specific formulary; lead↔survey was excluded because leads are pre-enrollment). The status_history links use a polymorphic pattern (entity_type + entity_id) which is operationally realistic for audit trail tables. Column removal was conservative but justified where clear redundancy exists (contract_number fields when adding contract_id FK). No M:N relationships were identified as genuinely HIGH confidence in this domain - most relationships are clear 1:N hierarchies. Minor uncertainty exists on whether some relationships (e.g., tax_detail→regulatory_filing) should be direct FK vs. many-to-many, but the 1:N model chosen reflects standard regulatory reporting patterns where tax details are reported in filings."
