"PRODUCT_DOMAIN_LOCATION_FIT","16","*","*","92","I conducted a thorough analysis of all 9 products in the government domain against the severity threshold criteria. Each product was evaluated for: (1) semantic relationship with government domain, (2) whether the product name/concept clearly belongs elsewhere, (3) whether current placement represents a data modeling error, and (4) parent-child relationships. All products are appropriately placed in the government domain because they represent government-program-specific implementations (Medicare, Medicaid, CHIP) with unique CMS regulatory requirements, distinct from general operations or commercial products. While some concepts (claims, eligibility, contracts) exist in other domains, these are program-specific variants that belong to government program management. No severe misplacements were identified. The 92/100 score reflects high confidence in this thorough analysis using the correct 0-100 scale, with minor uncertainty only around whether program_claim and program_payment could theoretically be in operations domain - but division boundary rules and program-specific nature justify KEEP decisions."
